However Sudibyo said that the government has no intention to break the bank institution , adding the investigation is intended to determine who are the wrongdoers . 
" We will save Bank Indonesia and we will defend the central bank 's position and its credibility , but the wrongdoers in Bank Indonesia should be brought to justice if they are found guilty . 
This will be an evidence that the new government is consistent and serious in curbing corruption , " he said . 
Bank Indonesia now has been facing a tough criticism from the public as the bank failed to recollect its liquidity assistance -LBR- BLBI -RBR- mounting to 164.54 trillion rupiah -LBR- 23.4 billion U.S. dollars -RBR- which had been disbursed to the country 's troubled banks . 
